chemaxon.marvin.modules
Class PDBReader

java.lang.Object
  chemaxon.marvin.modules.PDBReader
public class PDBReader
extends java.lang.Object

Import module for PDB files, replaces old PdbImport. This new implementation provides faster import, better interpratation of PDB data and more compact storage for macromolecules.
Backward compatibility in terms of available functionalities is maintained.

Since:
4.0.2
Version:
4.0.2 27-Oct-2005
Author:
Miklos Vargyas

skipToNext

public boolean skipToNext()
Skips the remaining part of the current molecule and positions the file pointer to the next one. Use this method if an error occured but you want to continue reading the file. Note, that this method is rarely relevant for PDB structures as PDB files are seldom concatenated.

Returns:
true if the end of the current molecule is found, false if there is no chance to continue
